ass=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-03T00:20:47.000Z","msg":"自製災難都係災難<br />\n充分展現出中國人既韌性 <img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"8bb35c1ff522ded63a746e26c62b323b06da8881","tid":1044384,"uid":48083,"like":15,"dislike":0,"score":15,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-03-03T00:32:57.000Z","msg":"睇吓條黃乜乜寫埋咩閪文<br />\n屌那星啲共諜上哂位<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nChina&rsquo;s use of big data might actually make it less Big Brother-ish<br />\n<br />\nWhy the country&rsquo;s adoption of ever-more-intrusive technology could, paradoxically, lead to stronger civil liberties.<br />\n<br />\nby Yasheng Huang  August 22, 2018<br />\n<br />\n⋯⋯<span style=\"color: red;\">Big data would be a threat if Chinese citizens could be expected to have an abundanc</span>e of political and civil liberties in its absence. But China is a repressive, authoritarian society with or without big data. <span style=\"color: red;\">Technology has made the repression more precise, but precise repression might be an improvement over indiscriminate repression.</span><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.technologyreview.com/s/611814/chinas-use-of-big-data-might-actually-make-it-less-big-brother-ish/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.technologyreview.com%2Fs%2F611814%2Fchinas-use-of-big-data-might-actually-make-it-less-big-brother-ish%2F&d=96kHarChHvhp0Q8MKJCyEJktsUQkmpJZziL8xq2DbDY%3D&h=26f35aad\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.technologyreview.com/s/611814/chinas-use-of-big-data-might-actually-make-it-less-big-brother-ish/</a>"},{"pid":"bd9ed4a31de5855b379a05b5cafbd277efdb3838","tid":1044384,"uid":5715,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-03-03T00:43:09.000Z","msg":"佢以為依家啲中國人仲同以前一樣捱得咩